                            <a href="https://crossroadsfarm.org/support" class="header_overlay"><img src="/workspace/images/header/positively_impact.png" /></a></div><div id="column_left"><h3>Board Members</h3><div id="board-list"><ul><li class="odd"><h4>Russ Baker</h4><p><description><p>Russell D. Baker (Russ) is a native of Hillsdale County, growing up just a
couple of miles from where Crossroads Farm is located. He is a 1977 graduate
of Reading High School.</p>

<p>Russ is a graduate of Huntington (IN) University and then received his
master’s and doctoral degrees from Kent State and Ball State Universities.
He has worked in higher education throughout his professional career,
beginning with a position in the admissions office at Huntington University,
spending 18 years in various academic administrative positions at Indiana
Institute of Technology in Fort Wayne, and the last five years working at
Ivy Tech Community College. As of July 1, 2011, Russ accepted the position
of Associate Vice President of Academic Affairs at Ivy Tech’s central
administrative office in Indianapolis.</p>

<p>Russ is married to Dolly, whom he met while they were students at Huntington
College. They have two children, Brianna and Bryant, and are members of
Blackhawk Ministries in Fort Wayne.</p>

<p>It has been a great honor to get involved as a board member with Crossroads
Farm. I vividly remember when it was a working farm owned by Harold and Ruth
Ashton. Nearly 35 years later, it is exhilarating to experience first-hand
the impact of the Farm on kids from Hillsdale County.</p>

<p>During my teen years, the only exciting thing to do on weekends was go to a
teen dance club in Reading! I wish there had been a Crossroads Farm ministry
to give positive alternatives for kids back then. One of the biggest things
that seems to have changed in the last 30 years is that economic
opportunities are fewer and therefore, poverty and despair seems deeper.
While there are certainly exceptions, family structure seems more broken.
Crossroads Farm is playing a vital role in giving students hope through a
personal faith in Someone and something that transcends the grim realities
of their lives.</p></description></p><p style="clear:both"></p></li><li><h4>Mark  Bortz</h4><p><description><p>Mark Bortz lives in Brentwood Tennessee with his wife Anne.  They both have been involved in mentoring children to live a life according to biblical principles and they believe the youth of today are in need of direction, reasoning, and guidance… and getting youth involved in Christian activities and surrounding them with compassionate mentors is fundamental to keeping them on track.  Mark says “For the youth in the lower-mid-Michigan community, the Crossroads Farm project is a superior option to attract and engage these youth.”  Mark has 3 children ages 22, 14 and 12.  Guiding these 3 children has and is an important part of his life.</p></description></p><p style="clear:both"></p></li><li class="odd"><h4>Ron Cieslak</h4><p><description></description></p><p style="clear:both"></p></li><li><p><img src="https://crossroadsfarm.org/image/2/200/300/5/stephen_and_julie.jpg" /></p><h4>Stephen Hallgren</h4><p><description><p>Stephen is Lead Engineer for <a href="http://virb.com">Virb</a> and is passionate about furthering CRF’s influence and impact on the internet. <a href="http://teev.io">Stephen</a>, his wife Julie and their <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/teevio/collections/72157627122506082/">4 children</a> live in Albany, NY.</p></description></p><p style="clear:both"></p></li><li class="odd"><h4>Jeff Miller</h4><p><description></description></p><p style="clear:both"></p></li><li><p><img src="https://crossroadsfarm.org/image/2/200/300/5/dawn_routledge.jpg" /></p><h4>Dawn Routledge</h4><p><description><p>Read more about Dawn over on the <a href="http://crossroadsfarm.org/about/staff/">Staff about page</a>.</p></description></p><p style="clear:both"></p></li><li class="odd"><h4>Doug Routledge</h4><p><description><p>Read more about Doug over on the <a href="http://crossroadsfarm.org/about/staff/">Staff about page</a>.</p></description></p><p style="clear:both"></p></li></ul></div></div><div id="column_right"><div id="contact-schedule"><p class="barnyard">Sunday evenings from 6:30 to 8:30 pm</p><p class="trough">Tuesday evenings from 7:00 to 8:30 pm</p><p class="tutoring">Thursdays from 3:30 to 5:30 pm</p></div><div id="social"><div id="share_tweet"><a href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-count="horizontal" data-via="crossroadsfarm" data-related="dougthespeakerguy">Tweet</a><script type="text/javascript" src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></div><div id="follow_tweet"><a href="http://twitter.com/crossroadsfarm" class="twitter-follow-button" data-link-color="#9f1d00">Follow @crossroadsfarm</a><script src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" type="text/javascript"></script></div><iframe src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http://www.facebook.com/pages/Crossroads-Farm/134200663255" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; width:100%; height:30px" send="true" layout="button_count" show_faces="true"></iframe></div><div id="donate"><p><a href="https://www.networkforgood.org/donation/ExpressDonation.aspx?ORGID2=383477455"><img src="/workspace/images/donate.png" /></a></p></div><div id="redeem_dropcard"><p class="dropcards"><a href="/dropcards"></a></p></div><div id="download_newsletter"><p class="download"><a href="/workspace/&#10;&#9;&#9;&#9;&#9;nlspring15.pdf&#10;&#9;&#9;&#9;&#9;&#10;&#9;&#9;&#9;">Down On The Farm / Down On The Farm: Quarterly Newsletter of Crossroads Farm</a></p><p class="see_all"> </p></div><div class="module" style="text-align: center;padding-left: 0"><a href="http://www.faithvillage.com" title="Join The Conversation at FaithVillage.com!" target="_blank" id="fvb_contributor_me_120x200" style="margin-right: 20px"><img src="http://shared-assets.faithvillage.com/public/badge/?img=contributor_me_120x200" alt="Join The Conversation at FaithVillage.com!" border="0" /></a><a href="http://www.ecfa.org"><img src="/workspace/images/ecfa.g